div.div:
How to dynamically build the topnav and sidebars?
What happens today?
1. topnav.yml has structure explicitly defined
2. topnav.html imports topnav.yml's data ( {% assign topnav = site.data[page.topnav] %} )
What happens during site build, vs page rendering?
I think static html produced at build-time, so who cares if it takes a long time to build.
Straw-man build process...
jekyll reads _config.yaml and starts building.
To build and pages, it needs the fonrtmatter data from all of the pages.
So... start each page with a loop to grab the frontmatter from the entire site collection of pages and refer back to that dataset for any more looping through pages that is required.
Probably easiest to start with topnav.html since it seems to get built pretty early.
Create a few documents with enough frontmatter to create a few "libraries", with a few "documents" each.
See if that can work, then extend it to the sidebars.
